The White House will be celebrating Halloween on October 28, 2019. The event is open to military families and local schoolchildren with their parents. The South Portico will be decorated with enchanting forest trees, pumpkins, and Halloween-themed displays. President Trump and First Lady Melania Trump will hand out commemorative candy to the children. Various departments and agencies, including NASA, the Department of Agriculture, and the Department of the Interior, will have displays and activities for the kids to enjoy. The United States Postal Service will also have spooky collection boxes and a Postal truck for children to see. The United States Secret Service will bring in the Presidential Limo, known as "The Beast," and the United States Air Force Strolling Strings will provide musical entertainment. Certain items are not allowed on the White House grounds, but strollers, wheelchairs, umbrellas, and cameras are permitted. Medical items needed for medical purposes will also be allowed. Visitors can call the 24-hour information line for event updates.